race.comment: HILLSIDE MONARCH (8) has switched barns on a 382-day return. She was only beaten 1.3L at Northam on debut and just missed in a recent 1100m trial here. Has the inside gate and is well-placed and looks ready to fire. ROLL'EMUP (1) also resumes and was last seen 172 days ago beaten a whisker this track/trip from the front. He has scope for further improvement and can make the finish if presented on song. DIXIE PRINCESS (2) was unlucky not to have broken through last preparation and third-up should be ready to show more. Has a handy 3kg claim and is likely to race forward. SHE'SATROOPER (5) has had two starts back off a long break and maps better today. She's lightly raced and would be a hope at best.
